The paper discusses the use of bibliographic classifications in organizing and linking information on the web, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most relevant sub-category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR), as the paper discusses ways to structure and present information and formulate queries. Digital Libraries (cs.DL) is also relevant, as the paper discusses the use of bibliographic classifications in resource discovery services on the web. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of classifications to assist computers in understanding and organizing information. Machine Learning (cs.LG) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of classifications to assist in information integration. Finally, Databases (cs.DB) is relevant as the paper discusses the technical limitations of bibliographic classifications.
